eventMaximumNumberOfEvents.name: eventMaximumNumberOfEvents
eventMaximumNumberOfEvents.description: The maximum number of event entries that can exist in the event table.

eventOldestEventIdNumber.name: eventOldestEventIdNumber
eventOldestEventIdNumber.description: The event ID number of the oldest event in the table. This value will be 0 until the first event occurs.

eventLatestEventIdNumber.name: eventLatestEventIdNumber
eventLatestEventIdNumber.description: The event ID number of the most recent event in the table. The SNMP manager should poll this variable periodically and compare it with the previous poll's value to detect the presence of new events. A value of 0 indicates no events exist in the table.

eventEntry.name: eventEntry
eventEntry.description: An entry containing object variables which describes an event.

eventIdNumber.name: eventIdNumber
eventIdNumber.description: A unique number assigned to every event entry. Numbers are assigned incrementally starting with 1 and will wraparound if the upper limit (2147483648) is reached. Until number wraps around, it represents the total number of events generated.

eventTimeStamp.name: eventTimeStamp
eventTimeStamp.description: The time of occurence for this event in seconds since startup. Use 'sysAbsoluteStartupTime' to convert to absolute time.

eventType.name: eventType
eventType.description: Identifies the type of event associated with this entry. For incoming MPP calls, the initial serviceChanged(4) event will be ppp(3). After negotiations complete, the nameChanged(5) event will specify mpp(5) along with the name, IP addr, and netmask.

eventCallReferenceNum.name: eventCallReferenceNum
eventCallReferenceNum.description: A unique number assigned to identify a particular session. The start of a session is marked by either a callOriginated(1) or a callAnswered(2) event. The end of a session is marked by a callCleared(3) event. Numbers are assigned incrementally starting with 1 and will wraparound if the upper limit (2147483648) is reached.

eventDataRate.name: eventDataRate
eventDataRate.description: The receive data rate for ISDN calls or the baud rate for modem calls. Rate is given as bits-per-second. Applicable for all 'eventType's except callCleared(3). For callCleared(3), 0 will be returned. For modem calls, value will be 0 for callAnswered(2) events since rate is unknown at the time incoming call is detected.

eventSlotNumber.name: eventSlotNumber
eventSlotNumber.description: Identifies the slot containing the line call was received or sent over. It's value ranges between 1 and the value slotNumber in the 'slots' group. This variable is equivalent to slotIndex in Ascend's slot group. Applicable only if 'eventType' is callOriginated(1), callAnswered(2), callCleared(3), or baudRateChanged(6) otherwise 0 will be returned.

eventSlotLineNumber.name: eventSlotLineNumber
eventSlotLineNumber.description: Identifies the line for network slots. This variable is equivalent to slotItemIndex in Ascend's slot group. Applicable only if 'eventType' is callOriginated(1), callAnswered(2), callCleared(3), or baudRateChanged(6) otherwise 0 will be returned.

eventSlotChannelNumber.name: eventSlotChannelNumber
eventSlotChannelNumber.description: Identifies the channel for the particular line identified by eventSlotLineNumber. Applicable only if 'eventType' is callOriginated(1), callAnswered(2), callCleared(3), or baudRateChanged(6) otherwise 0 will be returned.

eventModemSlotNumber.name: eventModemSlotNumber
eventModemSlotNumber.description: Identifies the modem slot on the device. It's value ranges between 0 and the value slotNumber in Ascend's slots group. A value of 0 indicates modems are not associated with this connection. Applicable only if 'eventType' is callOriginated(1), callAnswered(2), or baudRateChanged(6) otherwise 0 will be returned.

eventModemOnSlot.name: eventModemOnSlot
eventModemOnSlot.description: Identifies the particular modem within a modem slot. A value of 0 indicates modems are not associated with this connection. Applicable only if 'eventType' is callOriginated(1), callAnswered(2), or baudRateChanged(6) otherwise 0 will be returned.

eventCurrentService.name: eventCurrentService
eventCurrentService.description: The current service provided to the remote user. Applicable only if 'eventType' is serviceChanged(4) or nameChanged(5) otherwise none(1) will be returned.

eventUserName.name: eventUserName
eventUserName.description: The name of the remote user. Applicable only if 'eventType' is serviceChanged(4) or nameChanged(5). The null string is returned if the name is unknown or if not applicable. For a Radius DNIS authenticated session, value of User-Name provided in Radius reply will be used if no second tier authentication is involved.

eventUserIPAddress.name: eventUserIPAddress
eventUserIPAddress.description: The IP address of the remote user or login host. Applicable only if 'eventType' is serviceChanged(4) nameChanged(5) or callCleared. Value of a raw tcp login host IP address is returned once a raw tcp connection was successfully connected earlier in a serviceChanged event. The value 0.0.0.0 is returned if address is unknown or if not applicable.

eventUserSubnetMask.name: eventUserSubnetMask
eventUserSubnetMask.description: The subnet mask of the remote user. Applicable only if 'eventType' is serviceChanged(4) or nameChanged(5). The value 0.0.0.0 is returned if mask is unknown or if not applicable.

eventDisconnectReason.name: eventDisconnectReason
eventDisconnectReason.description: Reason for call disconnecting. Applicable only if 'eventType' is callCleared(3) otherwise notApplicable(1) will be returned.

eventConnectProgress.name: eventConnectProgress
eventConnectProgress.description: State of the connection before disconnecting. Applicable only if 'eventType' is callCleared(3) otherwise prNotApplicable(1) will be returned.

eventCallCharge.name: eventCallCharge
eventCallCharge.description: The call charge for this user. Applicable only if 'eventType' is callCleared( 3 ) otherwise 0 will be returned. A value of 0 is returned if entry is invalid.

eventCalledPartyID.name: eventCalledPartyID
eventCalledPartyID.description: The called party ID. Applicable only if 'eventType' is callCleared(3), callAnswered(2) or callOriginated(2) The null string is returned if the called party ID is unknown or if is not applicable.

eventCallingPartyID.name: eventCallingPartyID
eventCallingPartyID.description: The calling party ID. Applicable only if 'eventType' is callCleared(3), callAnswered(2) or callOriginated(2) The null string is returned if the calling party ID is unknown or if is not applicable.

eventInOctets.name: eventInOctets
eventInOctets.description: Identifies the total number of InOctets during this call. Applicable only if 'eventType' is callCleared(3), otherwise 0 will be returned.

eventOutOctets.name: eventOutOctets
eventOutOctets.description: Identifies the total number of OutOctets during this call. Applicable only if 'eventType' is callCleared(3), otherwise 0 will be returned.

eventMultiLinkID.name: eventMultiLinkID
eventMultiLinkID.description: MultiLinkID applies to sessions that are part of a Multilink bundle. Applicable if 'eventType' is callCleared(3), serviceChanged(4) or nameChanged(5) else 0 will be returned.

eventXmitRate.name: eventXmitRate
eventXmitRate.description: The transmit data rate for ISDN calls or the baud rate for modem calls. Rate is given as bits-per-second. Applicable for all 'eventType's except callCleared(3). For callCleared(3), 0 will be returned. For modem calls, value will be 0 for callAnswered(2) events since rate is unknown at the time incoming call is detected.

eventTrunkGroup.name: eventTrunkGroup
eventTrunkGroup.description: Trunk Group Number for outgoing call only Applicable only if 'eventType' is callEstablished or callOrignated, otherwise 0 will be returned.

eventCurrentActiveCalls.name: eventCurrentActiveCalls
eventCurrentActiveCalls.description: The number of calls currently active.

eventCurrentActiveSessions.name: eventCurrentActiveSessions
eventCurrentActiveSessions.description: The number of sessions currently active.

eventTotalCalls.name: eventTotalCalls
eventTotalCalls.description: The total number of active calls since system startup.

eventTotalSessions.name: eventTotalSessions
eventTotalSessions.description: The total number of active sessions since system startup.

eventTotalCallsAnswered.name: eventTotalCallsAnswered
eventTotalCallsAnswered.description: The total number of calls answered since system startup.

eventTotalCallsOriginated.name: eventTotalCallsOriginated
eventTotalCallsOriginated.description: The total number of calls originated since system startup.

eventTotalCallsCleared.name: eventTotalCallsCleared
eventTotalCallsCleared.description: The total number of calls cleared since system startup.

eventTotalBaudRateChanges.name: eventTotalBaudRateChanges
eventTotalBaudRateChanges.description: The total number of baud rate change events since system startup.

eventTotalServiceChanges.name: eventTotalServiceChanges
eventTotalServiceChanges.description: The total number of service change events since system startup.

eventTotalNameChanges.name: eventTotalNameChanges
eventTotalNameChanges.description: The total number of name change events since system startup.

eventTotalNoModems.name: eventTotalNoModems
eventTotalNoModems.description: The total number of unaccepted calls because of the unavailability of modems, since system startup.
